cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about neural sequence labeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also focuses on comparing different neural models, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the design challenges and misconceptions in neural sequence labeling, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions statistical experiments, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses benchmarks related to part-of-speech tagging and named entity recognition, which could be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
